Gold Rises on ECB Plan to Bolster Bank Lending, Erasing Drop of Up to 0.5%

-- B y   P a t r i c k   M c K i e r n a n
-- 
2011-12-07T13:43:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/gold-rises-on-ecb-plan-to-bolster-bank-lending-erasing-drop-of-up-to-0-5-.html
Gold rebounded after the  European
Central Bank  was said to be planning to announce a range of
measures to bolster lending.  Gold futures for February delivery rose $8.80, or 0.5
percent, to $1,740.60 an ounce at 8:42 a.m. on the Comex in  New
York , Earlier, the metal dropped as much as 0.5 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Patrick McKiernan at 
 pmckiernan@bloomberg.net  